    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "abc74fad_ce6a5c96",
        "filename": "src/chromiumos/tast/cmd/tast-lint/check/forbidden_calls.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 133,
      "author": {
        "id": 1118346
      },
      "writtenOn": "2021-06-01T08:55:03Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As you see, in general, it is impossible to safely add new imports... there can be local variables colliding import aliases, or there might be an existing import whose package name is not obvious from an import path (for example, the package name of \"foo/bar/baz\" can be \"errors\"). Thus we don\u0027t need to try too hard to cover all edge cases.\n\nSo I think the proposed approach is good; it is obviously wrong to treat \".\" or \"_\" as an import alias so it\u0027s nice to reject them. But in the real world, this branch would be rarely used since dot-imports are forbidden by golint and it is meaningless to underscore-import chromiumos/tast/errors.",
      "parentUuid": "7aeb5b4a_a3060a8b",
