      "writtenOn": "2021-06-09T02:30:35Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree with Oleh. I think tast-lint and IDEs have different expectations for auto imports... IDEs expect that users continue to edit the code and rename auto-generated aliases as they go, but tast-lint is usually run at the very last stage of patch preparation (just before uploading patches to Gerrit) and users are likely to apply the suggested change as-is when it is available. And we don\u0027t want users to keep auto-generated aliases like errors1.\n\nIn that case I think tast-lint can just refuse to auto-fix. Then users are forced to think of a good alias to use.",
      "parentUuid": "7bf2b9f2_14f9a099",
